------------------------------------
README
------------------------------------

Example of a global shakemovie simulation (see http://global.shakemovie.princeton.edu)

This example creates a global mesh, using a 3D shear-wave speed model S362ANI (Kustowski et al. [2006], 
and runs a spectral-element simulation. The simulation is setup to use 384 CPU cores (MPI processes).
The runtime is about 2h 30min.


1. forward simulation:
----------------------

type:
./run_this_example.sh

to setup this directory for the simulation and to run a corresponding
script "run_mesher_solver.bash".

The simulation is accurate down to a shortest period of ~ 17 s.
(minimum period resolved ~ (256/NEX_XI) * 17)
 
Reference seismograms for comparisons are provided in the directory: REF_SEIS/


Please modify the setup and scripts according to your specifics.

